      "side": 1,
      "message": "Continue For Loop If is deprecated since Robot Framework 5.0. The rest of the file already uses native IF/ELSE/END blocks. Using the deprecated keyword is inconsistent and will generate runtime deprecation warnings.\n\n```\nIF  \u0027${RESOURCE_TYPE_FILTER}\u0027 !\u003d \u0027${EMPTY}\u0027 and \u0027${resource_type}\u0027 !\u003d \u0027${RESOURCE_TYPE_FILTER}\u0027\n    CONTINUE\nEND\n```\n\nRF 5.0 introduced native IF blocks and CONTINUE to replace the old keyword-based control flow. Deprecated keywords will be removed in a future RF release.",
      "revId": "74a2459f1ff2792ea979fe9fc81c2f440a12e7af",
